# Keyboard Layout Rules (React Native — iOS + Android)

Apply whenever a screen or component has **`TextInput`**, **multiline inputs (textarea)**, **chat composers**, or **sticky bottom CTAs** that must stay visible above the keyboard.

**Install kit:** `node .cursor/scripts/setup-keyboard-layout.js` (runs automatically in project scaffold + socket agent).

---

## Required components (do not use KeyboardAvoidingView alone)

| Pattern | Layout | When |
| ------- | ------ | ---- |
| **Forms / ScrollView** | `KeyboardAwareLayout` from `@layouts/KeyboardAwareLayout` | Login, Create Ticket, settings, any scrollable form |
| **Chat / fixed footer** | `ChatKeyboardLayout` from `@layouts/ChatKeyboardLayout` | Socket chat, messaging, composer + FlatList |
| **Hooks** | `useKeyboardHeight`, `useKeyboardInsets` | Custom layouts only when layouts cannot wrap |

**Do not** rely on `KeyboardAvoidingView` alone for bottom inputs — it fails on Android with native stack + gesture nav.

---

## Form / ScrollView pattern (mandatory)

```javascript
import BaseScreen from '@layouts/BaseScreen';
import KeyboardAwareLayout from '@layouts/KeyboardAwareLayout';

<BaseScreen edges={['top', 'left', 'right']}>
  <KeyboardAwareLayout>
    {(insets) => (
      <ScrollView
        keyboardShouldPersistTaps="handled"
        keyboardDismissMode="on-drag"
        contentContainerStyle={{ paddingBottom: insets.scrollPaddingBottom }}>
        <TextInput />
      </ScrollView>
    )}
  </KeyboardAwareLayout>
</BaseScreen>
```

**Sticky submit footer:**

```javascript
<KeyboardAwareLayout footer={<PrimaryButton />}>
  {(insets) => (
    <ScrollView contentContainerStyle={{ paddingBottom: insets.scrollPaddingBottom }}>
      <TextInput />
    </ScrollView>
  )}
</KeyboardAwareLayout>
```

---

## Chat pattern (mandatory)

```javascript
import ChatKeyboardLayout from '@layouts/ChatKeyboardLayout';

<BaseScreen edges={['top', 'left', 'right']}>
  <ChatKeyboardLayout footer={composer}>
    {(insets) => (
      <FlatList
        contentContainerStyle={{ paddingBottom: insets.listPaddingBottom }}
        keyboardShouldPersistTaps="handled"
        automaticallyAdjustKeyboardInsets={false}
      />
    )}
  </ChatKeyboardLayout>
</BaseScreen>
```

---

## How it works (cross-platform)

1. **`useKeyboardHeight`** — uses `endCoordinates.screenY` (accurate on Android + iOS).
2. **Footer pinned** — `position: 'absolute', bottom: keyboardHeight` (open) or `insets.bottom` (closed).
3. **Scroll/list padding** — `scrollPaddingBottom` / `listPaddingBottom` = footer height + keyboard/safe-area space.
4. **`BaseScreen edges={['top','left','right']}`** — bottom inset handled by keyboard layout, not SafeAreaView.

---

## Agent checklist (coding / fixing / socket)

- [ ] `setup-keyboard-layout.js` installed (or run before implementing inputs)
- [ ] No screen with inputs uses raw `KeyboardAvoidingView` without `KeyboardAwareLayout` / `ChatKeyboardLayout`
- [ ] `keyboardShouldPersistTaps="handled"` on scroll/list containers
- [ ] `automaticallyAdjustKeyboardInsets={false}` when using `ChatKeyboardLayout` (manual insets own the layout)
- [ ] Android `AndroidManifest.xml` has `android:windowSoftInputMode="adjustResize"` (scaffold default)

---

## Out of scope

- Web / Next.js (use `.cursornext/` patterns separately)
- Modals with inputs — apply same `KeyboardAwareLayout` inside modal content
